            "text": "A Place That Remembers How to Slow Down",
            "size": "3xl"
          }
        },
        "welcome-text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Hearthstone is a ten-room guesthouse in a restored 1896 manor house, set on two acres of gardens in Rhinebeck, New York. The rooms are quiet. The mornings are unhurried. The details are the kind you notice on the second or third visit — wide-plank floors, original hardware, light that moves through the house all day.</p><p>We kept what the house already had and added only what it needed. Every room has its own view, its own character, and a bed you will not want to leave.</p>",
            "size": "base"
          }
        },
